                <head>320. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On April 19, 1966, President <persName corresp="#p_JLB1">Johnson</persName>
                    signed into law House Joint Resolution 997, “To support United States
                    participation in relieving victims of hunger in India and to enhance India’s
                    capacity to meet the nutritional needs of its people.” <persName
                        corresp="#p_JLB1">Johnson</persName> noted that the legislation supported
                    and endorsed his recent offer to enlarge food shipments to India to help offset
                    the worst drought of the century. He called upon the governments of other
                    countries to join in the effort to meet the disaster. For text of <gloss
                        target="#t_PL1">P.L.</gloss> 89–406, issued as 80 Stat. 131, see <hi
                        rend="italic">American Foreign Policy: Current Documents, 1966, page
                        688.</hi>
                </p>
            </div>
